-- Celtic Beats Helsingborg to Reach Champions League Group Stage
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-08-29T20:53:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-29/celtic-beats-helsingborg-to-reach-champions-league-group-stage.html
Celtic defeated Helsingborg 2-0 to
advance to the group stage of soccer’s  Champions League .  Gary Hopper and Victory Wanyama scored in Glasgow as Celtic
completed a 4-0 win in the two-match qualifying playoff. The win
sends Celtic into the group stage of Europe’s elite club
competition for the first time since 2008.  CFR Club beat Basel 1-0 to complete a 3-1 win in their
playoff, Spartak Moscow won 3-2 on aggregate over Fenerbahce
following a 1-1 draw and  Dynamo Kiev  also advanced by a 4-3
count despite losing 2-1 to Monchengladbach. Lille and
Copenhagen are playing extra time tied 1-1.  The draw for the 32-team group stage will be held tomorrow
in Monaco.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  